Hi Retell team,

We're an EU-based customer (Mindrails UG, Berlin, Germany), currently
building phonbot.de — a B2B SaaS that uses Retell to provide a voice-
agent platform to small and mid-sized German businesses.

Under GDPR Article 28, we're required to have a signed Data Processing
Agreement in place with every processor that handles personal data on
our behalf, before we can put Retell in our production stack. Our
go-live target is mid-Q2 2026 and Retell is in our published sub-
processor list (https://phonbot.de/sub-processors/).

Could you please send us:

1. Your standard Data Processing Addendum (DPA) — pre-signed PDF
   preferred, or DocuSign link.

2. EU Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) — Module 3 (processor-to-
   processor), since Retell acts as our sub-processor for our customers'
   end-callers.

3. Confirmation of your current DPF (EU-US Data Privacy Framework)
   certification status, if any. We're tracking this on
   dataprivacyframework.gov but appreciate a direct statement for our
   internal Transfer Impact Assessment.

4. Confirmation that data sent through your API is NOT used to train
   any AI model — i.e. an explicit zero-retention / no-training
   commitment for API-tier traffic.

5. A list of any sub-processors you in turn rely on (LLM providers,
   telephony carriers, hosting), including the country each operates
   from. We need this for our own published sub-processor list.

